import math
import sys

p = int(sys.stdin.readline())
a = list(map(int, sys.stdin.readline().split()))
b = [0] * (p - 1)

for i in range(p - 1):
    for j in range(p - 1):
        b[i] = (b[i] + a[j] * math.pow(i + 1, p - 1 - j)) % p

print(*b)

import numpy as np

p = int(input())
a = np.array(list(map(int, input().split())), dtype=np.int32)

b = np.zeros(p, dtype=np.int32)

for i in range(p):
    b[i] = (a[i] + 1) % p

print(*b, sep=' ')
